text: Monroe County is a county in the U.S. state of Pennsylvania. As of the 2020 census, the population was 168,327. Its county seat is Stroudsburg. The county was formed from sections of Northampton and Pike counties. It is named in honor of James Monroe, the fifth President of the United States. ==References== Category:1830s establishments in Pennsylvania Category:1836 establishments in the United States Category:Pennsylvania counties
title: Monroe County, Pennsylvania
